    {
      "text": "A 25 year old man presents with small, painless papules on the inner surface of his lips. On examination, the papules are skin-coloured and located along the vermilion border. Which of the following is most likely the diagnosis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Tyson glands",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Meibomian gland dysfunction",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Montgomery tubercles",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Fordyce spots",
          "correct": true
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "D. Fordyce spots",
      "question_images": [
