    {
      "text": "A 45 year old woman presents to the dermatology clinic with complaints of persistent redness, flushing, and occasional papules and pustules on her face. She reports that her symptoms worsen with sun exposure and spicy foods. On examination, diffuse erythema is present on the central face, predominantly on the cheeks shown in the image. Based on the clinical presentation, what is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Acne vulgaris",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Lupus erythematosus",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Atopic dermatitis",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Rosacea",
          "correct": true
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "D. Rosacea",
      "question_images": [
        "https://image.prepladder.com/content/1voidtFGykmsIjCwRG3l1723027854.png"
      ],
      "explanation_images": [
